title: Deering Library Level 3: Libraries - Northwestern University
content: The elevator for Deering Level 3 is located in the Architecture Reading Room. The Charles Deering McCormick Library of Special Collections and University Archives is home to many of the Libraries' rarest materials, including manuscripts, archives, prints, artifacts, and all materials pertaining to Northwestern's history. The Charles Deering McCormick Library is open to the public and our collections are non-circulating. In order to view collection materials in-person, see Plan A Visit.
